  "title": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Achalasia"
  },
  "definition": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Achalasia is an oesophageal smooth muscle motility disorder characterised by a loss of peristalsis in the distal oesophagus and a failure of lower oesophageal sphincter (LES) relaxation. Basic mechanism is the degeneration of neurons (ganglion cells) in the myenteric plexuses in the oesophageal wall, but the cause is still unclear."
  },
